Name: congenital generalized lipodystrophy type 1
Definition: A congenital generalized lipodystrophy that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of AGPAT2 on chromosome 9q34.3.

Name: congenital generalized lipodystrophy type 2
Definition: A congenital generalized lipodystrophy that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of BSCL2 on chromosome 11q12.3.

Name: congenital generalized lipodystrophy type 3
Definition: A congenital generalized lipodystrophy that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of CAV1 on chromosome 7q31.2.

Name: congenital generalized lipodystrophy type 4
Definition: A congenital generalized lipodystrophy that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of CAVIN1 on chromosome 17q21.2.
